event: step.delta
data: {"index":0,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Interpreting User Intent**\n\nI've clarified the user's request. It seems they want me to generate a fantastic GeoCities page, as \"vete\" in Dutch translates to \"awesome\" or \"cool.\" This helps me grasp the desired tone and quality of the final output, now I know what to aim for.\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta"}

event: step.delta
data: {"index":0,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Clarifying Request Ambiguity**\n\nI've explored the possible interpretations of \"vete,\" settling on \"vette\" (cool) as the most likely intention, given the Dutch context. Now, I'm thinking about the possibilities for a retro, Geocities-style webpage, incorporating 90s aesthetics. I want to build a fully working retro GeoCities HTML page, with the essential elements. I am checking what files are available to me.\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta"}

