event: step.delta
data: {"index":3,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Considering GeoCities Creation**\n\nI'm currently focused on replicating the GeoCities aesthetic in `/geocities`. The goal is to build a Dutch-language personal webpage with that iconic 90s vibe. I'm exploring the defining elements of a \"vet\" (cool) GeoCities page, as requested, to get it just right.\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta"}

event: step.delta
data: {"index":3,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Defining the Aesthetics**\n\nI've been identifying the key elements of a \"vet\" GeoCities page, specifically focusing on visual aspects. My current list centers around a dark or extremely loud background, animated GIFs (Under Construction, dancing figures, mailboxes), and text effects like marquee and blink (simulated with CSS). I am exploring bright, neon-colored fonts like Comic Sans and Impact, and also visitor counters. I plan to incorporate a guestbook and a webring too, and MIDI background music is also on the list.\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta","metadata":{"usage":{"total_tokens":6432,"total_input_tokens":5486,"input_tokens_by_modality":[{"modality":"text","tokens":5486}],"total_cached_tokens":0,"total_output_tokens":113,"output_tokens_by_modality":[{"modality":"text","tokens":113}],"total_tool_use_tokens":0,"total_thought_tokens":833}}}

event: step.delta
data: {"index":3,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Personalizing the Experience**\n\nI'm now diving into personalized content, and am tailoring the GeoCities page for Arthur Bleij, a real estate expert at Fakton. The humor of merging a financial consultancy with a 1996 web aesthetic is irresistible. I plan to add a blinking \"NIEUW!\" badge, a \"Mijn Hobbies\" section (real estate, Excel, and Gabber music, among other things), and a spinning visitor counter. The page title will be \"Arthur's Mega Real-Estate & Finance GeoHome 1998\".\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta"}

event: step.delta
data: {"index":3,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Designing the Website**\n\nI'm now incorporating a guestbook with the ability for visitors to \"tekenen\" (sign) and am setting up webring links like \"Fakton Web Ring\" and \"Vastgoed Gilde.\" A \"vet\" mock Winamp-style MIDI player will be included, and I've decided to write `/geocities/index.html` with retro CSS styling, though I'm considering presenting the HTML in markdown to avoid the need to serve the file. I will write a script to generate all this.\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta"}

event: step.delta
data: {"index":3,"delta":{"content":{"text":"**Creating the Webpage**\n\nI've decided to create a single, self-contained HTML file for the GeoCities page. I'm focusing on crafting the look, with a tiled starfield background and a WordArt-style header. I'm building a CSS-only Winamp player and the main content will be inside a table. The marquee text is also ready to be added!\n\n\n","type":"text"},"type":"thought_summary"},"event_type":"step.delta"}

